Durban - Radical Economic Transformation (RET) Champion, a group of black business groups known for their backing of former president Jacob Zuma, says that Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan is a law unto himself and are calling for the African National Congress (ANC) to axe him as a cabinet minister. Nkosentsha Shezi, of RET Champion, is accusing Gordhan of “unleashing venom” against black managers at state-owned enterprises and has also blamed the ANC for remaining silent. On Monday, the group and its supporters is set to picket outside Luthuli House to pressure the ANC into firing Gordhan. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
